This artifact vendors an ai-memory lifecycle hook from akitaonrails/ai-memory.

Vendored (upstream paths):
  - hooks/claude-code/pre-tool-use.sh  (the hook body)
  - hooks/_lib.sh              (shared helpers, INLINED into the script above —
                               Patronus places one script per hook, with no
                               shared sibling, so the helpers are concatenated in)

Adaptations: the upstream `. "$_lib_dir/_lib.sh"` source lines were removed and
the _lib.sh helper functions inlined verbatim; the agent id is fixed to
claude-code. Behavior is otherwise unchanged.

Audit: the script POSTs the hook event JSON to the LOCAL ai-memory server only
($AI_MEMORY_HOOK_URL, default http://127.0.0.1:49374) with a 0.5-1s timeout,
fire-and-forget (`|| true`). It makes no external network calls, runs no eval,
and performs no destructive filesystem operations; _lib.sh is read-only path/TOML
parsing that stops at $HOME.

Upstream: https://github.com/akitaonrails/ai-memory
